CCCCHHEEAADD -- Environmental Variable

Append options to beginning of cc command line
eexxppoorrtt CCCCHHEEAADD=_o_p_t_i_o_n_s

The  COHERENT compiler  cccc  reads the  environmental  variables CCCCHHEEAADD  and
CCCCTTAAIILL before it begins its work.   You can set these variables to hold the
default options that you want the compiler always to use.

cccc appends the options in CCCCHHEEAADD to the beginning of its command line.

_S_e_e _A_l_s_o
cccc, CCCCTTAAIILL, eennvviirroonnmmeennttaall vvaarriiaabblleess
